this folder contains two projects: whizvoice which is a webserver, and whizvoiceapp which is an Android app.
Please don't downgrade packages for no reason.
Whenever you change any production files in whizvoiceapp please also run `cd whizvoiceapp && ./android_hot_reload.sh` to kick off the build in Android Studio so we can test the change right away. If you are just changing test files, there's no need to run the hot reload, but you should probably run the tests to see if they work.
Please change files right away whenever you think they need to be changed. There is no need to ask for confirmation. There is no need to ask me to accept the changes either - just do it. I am using an IDE that will automatically show me any changes you made for me to review.
If you need to read files to understand how to change them to fix the problem, please do so. There is no need to ask for confirmation.
Don't try to restart the server yourself - just ask me to do it. It's on a different machine.
Please leave git commit and git push to me, though I may need your help merging sometimes.

We use supabase for the database. There's a users table, a user_preferences table, a conversations table, and a messages table.

users table:

id | int8
created_at | timestamp | now()
email | text
user_id | text
google_assistant_user_id | text

the user ID is given by google auth, and is a unique identifier for the user.

user_preferences table:

id | int8
created_at | timestamp | now()
user_id | text | foreign key to users.user_id
preferences | jsonb
encrypted_preferences | bytea
last_updated | timestamp | now()

conversations table:

id | int8
user_id | text | foreign key to users.user_id
title | text
created_at | timestamp | now()
last_message_time | timestamp | now()
source | text | 'app', 'voice', or 'web'
google_session_id | text
updated_at | timestamp | now()

This table also has indexes
- idx_conversations_user_id on conversations(user_id)
- idx_conversations_last_message on conversations(user_id, last_message_time DESC)
- idx_conversations_user_updated on conversations(user_id, updated_at DESC)

messages table:

id | int8
conversation_id | int8 | foreign key to conversations.id
content | text
message_type | text | 'USER' or 'ASSISTANT'
timestamp | timestamp | now()
updated_at | timestamp | now()

This table also has indexes
- idx_messages_conversation_id on messages(conversation_id)
- idx_messages_timestamp on messages(conversation_id, timestamp ASC)
- idx_messages_conversation_updated on messages(conversation_id, updated_at DESC)

sync_metadata table:

id | int8
user_id | text | foreign key to users.user_id
entity_type | text | 'conversations', 'messages'
entity_id | int8 | foreign key to conversations.id or messages.id
last_sync_timestamp | timestamp
created_at | timestamp | now()
updated_at | timestamp | now()

the combination of user_id, entity_type, and entity_id is unique.
